## Create View on Table ABAP Dictionary (SE11) {#create-view-on-table-abap-dictionary-(se11)}

Follow this procedure to create a [view](https://sapported.com/tutorials/technical/abap/how-to-create-table-view-in-transaction-se11/). 

Go to SE11, and create a view:  
![][image1]  
Choose Database view.  
Add a description  
In Table/Join Conditions as KNA1  
![][image2]  
In View Fields, select Table fields, select all, and copy. 

![][image3]  
Seems like too many fields for the next step.

In selection field just get the English description:  
![][image4]  
Activate the object (wand with sparkles)  
Local object, Accept.  
Warnings, display, Yes, back.  
Displays active.   
ZKNA1E

## Maintain Generic DataSources (RSO2) {#maintain-generic-datasources-(rso2)}

![][image5]  
Select Create.

Choose the application component where you want the generic source to go (**FI**).  
![][image6]  
Save

## Extractor Checker S-API (RSA3) {#extractor-checker-s-api-(rsa3)}

Go to transaction RSA3.  
Enter the name data source (KNA1).  
![][image7]  
Execute. The number of data records selected appears. Select ok.  
Select ALV Grid to see the data records.  
![][image8]

## Data Browser Check External Exposure (ROOSATTR in SE16) {#data-browser-check-external-exposure-(roosattr-in-se16)}

Go to transaction SE16.  
Add the table name ROOSATTR and hit return.  
Enter the name of the extractor you created (ZKNA1).  The table is filtered on that, and you see KNA1 is exposed.  
![][image9]
